83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
HOUSE AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4029
By COMMITTEE ON CLIMATE, ENERGY, AND ENVIRONMENT
February 11
1 On page 1 of the printed bill, line 21, after the second “electrician,” insert “a limited residential
2 electrician,”.
3 On page 7, after line 11, insert:
4 “(6) If a solar energy contractor or the person that installs a solar energy system provides a
5 warranty under subsection (2)(m) of this section, the warranty must transfer to a purchaser of the
6 residential real property to which the warranty applies and remain in effect for the duration of the
7 warranty term.”.
8 On page 11, after line 2, insert:
9 “(4) If a solar energy contractor or the person that installs a solar energy system provides a
10 warranty for repairs to a resident’s property as a consequence of the installation or removal of the
11 solar energy system, the warranty must transfer to a purchaser of the residential real property to
12 which the warranty applies and remain in effect for the duration of the warranty term.”.
